  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Remove the leaves from your <strong>cauliflower</strong>, then chop into rough bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the<strong> cauliflower </strong>to a<strong> food processor</strong> and blitz until finely chopped – this is your <strong>cauliflower rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1588591111043-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1588591111043-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1588591111043-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1588591111043-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1588591111043-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cover your <strong>blanched peas</strong> with <strong>boiled water</strong> and set aside until later</p><p>Grate your <strong>carrot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1588591114667-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1588591114667-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1588591114667-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1588591114667-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1588591114667-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> chicken breast strips</strong> into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped chicken</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until browned all over</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1588591118265-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1588591118265-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1588591118265-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1588591118265-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1588591118265-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>peas</strong>, then add them to the pan with the <strong>grated carrot</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1588591121935-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1588591121935-x400.jpg",
